# Before committing a new release version, build to update the lib directory
- Change things
- then from the root of the project ...

## For RN New Arch
- Note: these notes were taken for RNMaps v1.26.10 RN v0.81.1

- Install stuff
yarn

- Build TypeScript (so the spec file is discoverable)
yarn build

- Run the codegen artifact generator
npx react-native codegen

-- iOS
-- NOTE: there is some kind of a kink in configs or commands that makes the CLI
-- codegen command fail and not place the files where they are suppose to be, it
-- fails semi-silently with "[Codegen] Done." output, but it does throw an error
-- "[Codegen] TypeError [ERR_INVALID_ARG_TYPE]: The "from" argument must be of type string. Received undefined"
-- So run the following iOS specific command to generate codegen files
-- ATTENTION: do NOT remove dir ios/generated
node ./node_modules/react-native/scripts/generate-codegen-artifacts.js -p . -o ./ios/generated -t ios -s library -n RNMapsSpecs -c

- Run
yarn bootstrap

---

# Test the example app
- After your changes and ran all the build, codegen and bootstrap commands, if
- you wish to test the example app with your new changes:

- Setup example app with Google MAPS_API_KEY for both iOS and Android
file://./docs/examples-setup.md
